In Bulgaria, abortion is socially and culturally accepted, and the consequences in practice — for the woman and for the family — are often devastating. Statistics by the World Health Organization show that about 20% of AIDs cases in Bulgaria are associated with abortion — dysmenorrhea, large hemorrhages after surgery, damage to the reproductive organs and negative psychological effects are also known as among the complications of an abortion in Bulgaria, which are often under-diagnosed by the abortionist.

Many times [Bulgaria], able-bodied women, [are] compelled as “debt slaves”, to have multiple abortions in order to protect a man they don’t love, to save their family or their country. Often, a small or large breach of conscience sends them on a heroic odyssey to stand up for their own lives, the lives of their children, their parents, their spouse or their country.

The motto of Abortion Free Bulgaria is “There is no future in abortions.” Over the next year, they will use bans on abortion, restrictions on abortion, education of young people, registration of the BAPKiM workers, doctors, lawyers, theologians, psychologists, doctors and others who will join the pro-life team in defense of the sanctity of life.
